HMS Victory

by Peter Edwards

 Instructions.
Hint - examine everything. The pictures are not just for decoration.
Oh yes, and be kind to seagulls. Some say that they are the spirits of dead seamen...

You are standing outside The Keppel's Head, an historic pub near Portsmouth dockyard.

Good luck and bon voyage!

(Press any key to enter the inn)

You are in The Keppels Head.

You are sitting in The Keppel's Head enjoying a quiet drink when suddenly you are joined by a sailor dressed in 18th Century Royal Navy uniform. He tells you that he and his shipmates had served with Nelson in all his campaigns and the Great Man had promised them all an honourable discharge on arriving back in England. Unfortunately the Admiral had been killed before the promise could be ratified.

"So you see, matee, me and me shipmates are now doomed to haunt Portsmouth for all eternity unless some brave soul can find the Admiral's eight special objects and return them to his cabin. So now, my hearty, do you lay a S'uthard course for the good ship Victory and Save Our Souls".

You try to ask what these objects are and where they can be found, but with a whisper of "Don't 'e let us down now, matee...", the ghost disappears like a whiff of smoke.
